For my first trip to Key West we decided to stay at the Fairfield Inn and Suites - I was extremely disappointed in the rooms.	It was unfortunate that our stay could not have been longer, maybe next time and I certainly would consider staying at the Fairfield again.	We almost always stay at Marriott hotels and when we saw the Fairfield Inn and Suites in Key West was a category 5, we made a reservation for two nights.	If I have the opportunity to stay in Key West again, I would certainly consider this hotel.	I've stayed at the Fairfield previously and booked this trip for a retirement celebration with a family member.